<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="271" pageId="13" pageNumber="270" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[813,1456,1871,2028]" box="[813,903,1871,1897]" pageId="13" pageNumber="270">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[813,1456,1871,2028]" lastBlockId="14.[132,775,1267,1326]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="271" pageId="13" pageNumber="270">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perrier" authorityYear="1875" box="[813,946,1903,1929]" class="Asteroidea" family="Asteriidae" genus="Asterias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Forcipulatida" pageId="13" pageNumber="270" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="borbonica">
<emphasis box="[813,946,1903,1929]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="270">A. borbonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[954,1049,1903,1929]" pageId="13" pageNumber="270">holotype</typeStatus>
is a juvenile specimen having the appearance and skeletal organization of an echinasterid individual. Its reticulated abactinal skeleton tends to arrange in longitudinal series as in some 
<taxonomicName box="[1143,1340,2001,2027]" class="Asteroidea" family="Echinasteridae" genus="Echinaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spinulosida" pageId="13" pageNumber="270" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1143,1250,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="270">Echinaster</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
Giving its geographical origin, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perrier" authorityYear="1875" box="[351,483,1267,1294]" class="Asteroidea" family="Asteriidae" genus="Asterias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Forcipulatida" pageId="14" pageNumber="271" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="borbonica">
<emphasis box="[351,483,1267,1294]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="271">A. borbonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could belong to the species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perrier" authorityYear="1869" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[132,348,1299,1325]" class="Asteroidea" family="Echinasteridae" genus="Echinaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spinulosida" pageId="14" pageNumber="271" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="purpureus">
<emphasis box="[132,348,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="271">Echinaster purpureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
